fields.caption: Title
fields.description: The title of the resource

fields.caption: Subject
fields.description: An unordered array of keywords that specify the topic of the content of the resource

fields.caption: Description
fields.description: A textual description of the content of the resource

fields.caption: Creator
fields.description: The authors of the resource  (listed in order of precedence, if significant).

fields.caption: Publishers
fields.description: Publishers

fields.caption: Contributor
fields.description: Contributors to the resource (other than the authors)

fields.caption: Format
fields.description: The file format used when saving the resource (MIME Type)

fields.caption: Type
fields.description: Resource type: for example, novel, poem, etc...

fields.caption: Related
fields.description: Relation with other resources

fields.caption: Languages
fields.description: An unordered array specifying the languages used in the resource

fields.caption: Identifier
fields.description: Unique identifier of the resource

fields.caption: Rights
fields.description: Informal rights statement, selected by language

fields.caption: Source
fields.description: Unique identifier of the work from which this resource was derived

fields.caption: Coverage
fields.description: The extent or scope of the resource

fields.caption: Date
fields.description: Date(s) that something interesting happened to the resource

fields.caption: Creation date
fields.description: The date and time the resource was originally created.

fields.caption: Rating
fields.description: Resource user rating value

fields.caption: Modify Date
fields.description: The date and time the resource was last modified

fields.caption: Advisory
fields.description: An unordered array specifying properties that were edited outside the authoring application. Each item should contain a single namespace and XPath separated by one ASCII space.

fields.caption: Baseurl
fields.description: The base URL for relative URLs in the document content. If this document contains Internet links, and those links are relative, they are relative to  this base URL.

fields.caption: Creator Tool
fields.description: The name of the first known tool used to create the resource. Same as tiff:Software.

fields.caption: Identifier
fields.description: An unordered array of text strings that unambiguously identify the resource within a given context.

fields.caption: Label
fields.description: A word or short phrase that identifies a document  as a menber of a user-defined collection. Used to organize documents in a file browser.

fields.caption: Metadatadate
fields.description: The date and time that any metadata for this resource was last changed.

fields.caption: Nickname
fields.description: A short  informal name for the resource.

fields.caption: Owners
fields.description: An unordered array specifying the legal owner(s) of the resource

fields.caption: Protected
fields.description: Indicates that this is a rights managed resource

fields.caption: Usage terms
fields.description: Legal usage terms

fields.caption: Web Statement
fields.description: Web link to the rights descriptions

fields.caption: Web certificate
fields.description: Online rights management certificate.

fields.caption: Max Page Size
fields.description: The size of the largest page in the document(including any in contained documents).

fields.caption: Number Of Pages
fields.description: The number of pages in the document(including any in contained documents).

fields.caption: Plate Names
fields.description: An ordered array of plate names that are needed to print the document(including any in contained documents).

fields.caption: Project Reference
fields.description: A reference to the project that created this file.

fields.caption: Frame rate
fields.description: The video frame rate. One of 24, NTSC,PAL.

fields.caption: Framesize
fields.description: The frame size.

fields.caption: Aspect ratio
fields.description: The aspect ratio, expressed as ht/wd.

fields.caption: Pixel depth
fields.description: The size in bits of each color component of a pixel.

fields.caption: Color space
fields.description: The color space.

fields.caption: Alpha mode
fields.description: The alpha mode.

fields.caption: Alpha unity is transparent
fields.description: When 'true', unity is clear, when 'false', it is opaque.

fields.caption: Video compressor
fields.description: Video compression used.

fields.caption: Field order
fields.description: The field orderfor video.

fields.caption: Pull down
fields.description: The sampling phase of film to be converted to video.

fields.caption: Sample rate
fields.description: The audio sample rate.

fields.caption: Audio sample type
fields.description: The audio sample type.

fields.caption: Channel type
fields.description: The audio Channel Type.

fields.caption: Compressor
fields.description: The audio compression used. For example, MP3.

fields.caption: Speaker placement
fields.description: A description of the speaker angles from center front in degrees.

fields.caption: File data rate
fields.description: The file data rate in megabytes per second.

fields.caption: Tape name
fields.description: The name of the tape from which the clip was captured, as set during the capture process.

fields.caption: Alternative tape name
fields.description: An alternative tape name, set via the project window or timecode dialog in Premiere.

fields.caption: Duration
fields.description: The duration of the media file.

fields.caption: Scene
fields.description: The name of the scene.

fields.caption: Shot name
fields.description: The name of the shot or take.

fields.caption: Shot date
fields.description: The date and time  when the video was shot.

fields.caption: Shot location
fields.description: The name of the location where the video was shot.

fields.caption: Log comment
fields.description: User's log comments.

fields.caption: Absolute peak audio filepath
fields.description: The absolute path to the file's peak audio file. If empty, no peak file exists.

fields.caption: Relative peak audio filepath
fields.description: The relative path to the file's peak audio file. If empty, no peak file exists.

fields.caption: Video modifie date
fields.description: The date and time when the video was last modified.

fields.caption: Audio modifie date
fields.description: The date and time when the audio was last modified.

fields.caption: Metadata modifie date
fields.description: The date and time when the metadata was last modified.

fields.caption: Artist
fields.description: the name of the artist or artists.

fields.caption: Album
fields.description: The name of the album.

fields.caption: Track number
fields.description: A numeric value indicating the order of the audio file within its original recording.

fields.caption: Genre
fields.description: The name of the genre.

fields.caption: Copyright
fields.description: The copyright information.

fields.caption: Release date
fields.description: The date the title was released.

fields.caption: Composer
fields.description: The composer's name.

fields.caption: Engineer
fields.description: The engineer's name.

fields.caption: Tempo
fields.description: The audio's tempo.

fields.caption: Instrument
fields.description: The musical instrument.

fields.caption: Intro time
fields.description: The duration of lead time for queuing music.

fields.caption: Out cue
fields.description: The time at which to fade out.

fields.caption: Relative timestamp
fields.description: The start time of the media inside the audio  project.

fields.caption: Loop
fields.description: When true, the clip can be looped seemlessly.

fields.caption: Number of beats
fields.description: The number of beats.

fields.caption: Key
fields.description: The audio's musical key.

fields.caption: Stretch mode
fields.description: The audio stretch mode.

fields.caption: Time signature
fields.description: The time segnature of the music.

fields.caption: Scale type
fields.description: The musical scale used in the music.

fields.caption: Keywords
fields.description: Keywords.

fields.caption: PDF Version
fields.description: The PDF file version.

fields.caption: Producer
fields.description: The name of the tool that created the PDF document.

fields.caption: Author Position
fields.description: By-line title.

fields.caption: Caption Writer
fields.description: Writer/editor.

fields.caption: Category
fields.description: Category. limited to 3 7-bit ascii characters.

fields.caption: City
fields.description: City.

fields.caption: Country
fields.description: Country/primary location.

fields.caption: Credit
fields.description: Credit.

fields.caption: Date Created
fields.description: The date the intellectual content was originally created (rather than the  creation date of the physical representation).

fields.caption: Headline
fields.description: Headline.

fields.caption: Instructions
fields.description: Special instructions.

fields.caption: Source
fields.description: Source.

fields.caption: State
fields.description: Province/state.

fields.caption: Supplemental Categories
fields.description: Supplemental category.

fields.caption: Trasmission Reference.
fields.description: Original trasmission reference.

fields.caption: Urgency
fields.description: Urgency. valid range is 1-8.

fields.caption: Auto Brightness
fields.description: When true, "Brightness" is automatically adjusted.

fields.caption: Auto Contrast
fields.description: When true, " Contrast" is automatically adjusted.

fields.caption: Auto Exposure
fields.description: When true, "AutoExposure" is automatically adjusted.

fields.caption: Auto Shadows
fields.description: When true, "AutoShadows" is automatically adjusted.

fields.caption: Blue Hue
fields.description: "BlueHue" setting. Range -100 to 100.

fields.caption: Blue Saturation
fields.description: "BlueSaturation" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Brightness
fields.description: "Brightness" setting. Range 0 to +150.

fields.caption: Camera Profile
fields.description: "CameraProfile" setting.

fields.caption: Chromatic Aberration B
fields.description: "Chromatic Aberration, Fix Blue/Yellow Fringe" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Chromatic Aberration R
fields.description: "Chromatic Aberration, Fix Red/Cyan Fringe" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Color Noise Reduction
fields.description: "Color Noise Reduction" setting. Range 0 to +100.

fields.caption: Contrast
fields.description: "Contrast" setting. Range -50 to +100.

fields.caption: Crop Top
fields.description: When HasCrop is true, top of crop rectangle.

fields.caption: Crop Left
fields.description: When HasCrop is true, left of crop rectangle.

fields.caption: Crop Bottom
fields.description: When HasCrop is true, bottom of crop rectangle.

fields.caption: Crop Right
fields.description: When HasCrop is true, right of crop rectangle.

fields.caption: Crop Angle
fields.description: When HasCrop is true, angle of crop rectangle.

fields.caption: Crop Width
fields.description: Width of resulting cropped image in Cropunits units.

fields.caption: Crop Height
fields.description: Height of resulting cropped image in Cropunits units.

fields.caption: Crop Units
fields.description: Units for CropWidth and CropHeight. One of: 0=pixels 1=inches 2=cm

fields.caption: Exposure
fields.description: "Exposure" setting. Range -4.0 to +4.0.

fields.caption: Green Hue
fields.description: "GreenHue" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Green Saturation
fields.description: "GreenSaturation" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Has Crop
fields.description: When true, image as a cropping rectangle.

fields.caption: Has Settings
fields.description: When true, non-default camera raw settings.

fields.caption: Luminance Smoothing
fields.description: "Luminance Smoothing" setting. Range 0 to +100.

fields.caption: Raw File Name
fields.description: File name fo raw file (not a complete path).

fields.caption: Red Hue
fields.description: "RedHue" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Red Saturation
fields.description: "RedSaturation" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Saturation
fields.description: "Saturation" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Shadows
fields.description: "Shadows" setting. range 0 to +100.

fields.caption: Shadows Tint
fields.description: "Shadows Tint" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Sharpness
fields.description: "Sharpness" setting. Range -100 to +100.

fields.caption: Temperature
fields.description: "Temperature" setting. Range 2000 to 50000.

fields.caption: Tint
fields.description: "Tint" setting. range -150 to +150.

fields.caption: ToneCurve
fields.description: Array of points (Integer, Integer) defining a "Tone Curve".

fields.caption: Tone Curve Name
fields.description: The name of the Tone Curve described by ToneCurve. One of : Linear, Medium Contrast, Strong Contrast, Custom or a user-defined preset name.

fields.caption: Version
fields.description: Version of Camera Raw plugin.

fields.caption: Vignette Amount
fields.description: "Vignetting Amount" setting. Range -100 to +100

fields.caption: Vignette Midpoint
fields.description: "Vignetting Midpoint" setting. Range 0 to +100.

fields.caption: White Balance
fields.description: "White Balance" setting. One of: As Shot, Auto, Daylight, Cloudy, Shade, Tungsten, Fluorescent, Flash, Custom

fields.caption: Width
fields.description: TIFF tag 256, 0x100. Image Width in pixels.

fields.caption: Height
fields.description: TIFF tag 257, 0x101. Image height in pixels.

fields.caption: Bits Per Sample
fields.description: TIFF tag 258, 0x102. Number of bits per component in each channel.

fields.caption: Compression
fields.description: TIFF tag 259, 0x103. Compression scheme: 1=uncompressed; 6=JPEG

fields.caption: Photometric Interpretation
fields.description: TIFF tag 262, 0x106. Pixel Composition: 2=RGB; 6=YCbCr

fields.caption: Orientation
fields.description: TIFF tag 274, 0x112.

fields.caption: Sample Per Pixel
fields.description: TIFF tag 277, 0x115. Number of components per pixel.

fields.caption: Planar Configuration
fields.description: TIFF tag 284, 0x11C. Data layout: 1 = chunky; 2 = planar

fields.caption: YCbCr SubSampling
fields.description: TIFF tag 530, 0x212. Sampling ratio of chrominance components: [2,1]= YCbCr4:2:2, [2,2]= YCbCr4:2:0.

fields.caption: YCbCr Positioning
fields.description: TIFF tag 531, 0x213. Position of chrominance vs. luminance components: 1= centered; 2= co-sited.

fields.caption: X Resolution
fields.description: TIFF tag 282, 0x11A. Horizontal resolution in pixels per unit.

fields.caption: Y Resolution
fields.description: TIFF tag 283, 0x11B. Vertical resolution in pixels per unit.

fields.caption: Resolution Unit
fields.description: TIFF tag 296, 0x128. Unit used for XResolution and YResolution. Value is one of: 2= inches; 3= centimeters.

fields.caption: Transfer Function
fields.description: TIFF tag 301, 0x12D. Transfer function for image described in tabular style with 3 * 256 entries.

fields.caption: White Point
fields.description: TIFF tag318, 0x13E. Chromaticity of white point.

fields.caption: Primary Chromaticities
fields.description: TIFF tag 319, 0x13F. Chromaticity of three primary colors.

fields.caption: YCbCr Coefficients
fields.description: TIFF tag 529, 0x211. Matrix coefficients for RGB to YCbCr transformation.

fields.caption: Reference Black/White
fields.description: TIFF tag 532, 0x214. Reference black and white point values.

fields.caption: DateTime
fields.description: Date/time the resource was last modified. This property is stored in XMP as xmp:ModifyDate.

fields.caption: Image Description
fields.description: TIFF tag 270, 0x10E. Description of the image.

fields.caption: Make
fields.description: TIFF tag 271, 0x10F. Manifacturer of recording equipment.

fields.caption: Model
fields.description: TIFF tag 272, 0x110. Model name or number of equipment.

fields.caption: Software
fields.description: TIFF tag 305, 0x131. Software or firmware used to generate image.

fields.caption: Artist
fields.description: TIFF tag 315, 0x13B. Camera owner, photographer or image creator.

fields.caption: Copyright
fields.description: TIFF tag 33432, 0x8298.Copyright information.

fields.caption: Latitude
fields.description: indicates latitude

fields.caption: Longitude
fields.description: iindicates longitudes

fields.caption: Exif Version
fields.description: EXIF tag 36864, 0x9000. EXIF version number.

fields.caption: Flash Pix Version
fields.description: EXIF tag 40960, 0xA000. Version of FlashPix.

fields.caption: Color Space
fields.description: EXIF tag 40961, 0xA001. Color Space information: 1= sRGB, 65535= uncalibrated.

fields.caption: Components Configuration
fields.description: EXIF tag 37121, 0x9101. Configuration of components in data: 4 5 6 0(if RGB compressed data), 1 2 3 0 (other cases).

fields.caption: Compressed Bits Per Pixel
fields.description: EXIF tag 37122, 0x9102. Compression mode used for a compressed image is indicated in unit bits per pixel.

fields.caption: Pixel X Dimension
fields.description: EXIF tag 40962, 0xA002. Valid image widht, in pixels.

fields.caption: Pixel Y Dimension
fields.description: EXIF tag 40963, 0xA003. Valid image height, in pixels.

fields.caption: User Comment
fields.description: EXIF tag 37510, 0x9286. Comments from user.

fields.caption: Related Sound File
fields.description: EXIF tag 40964, 0xA004.An "8.3" file name for the related sound file.

fields.caption: Original Date/Time
fields.description: Date and time when original image was taken.

fields.caption: Digitized Date/Time
fields.description: Date and time when the image was stored as digital data.

fields.caption: Exposure Time
fields.description: EXIF tag 33434, 0x829A. Exposure time in seconds.

fields.caption: F Number
fields.description: EXIF taf 33437, 0x829D.F Number.

fields.caption: Exposure Program
fields.description: EXIF tag 34850, 0x8822. Class of program used for exposure: 0=not defined, 1= Manual, 2=Normal Program, 3= Aperture priority, 4= Shutter priority, 5= Creative program, 6= Action program, 7=portrait mode, 8= Landscape mode

fields.caption: Spectral Sensitivity
fields.description: EXIF tag 34852, 0x8824. Spectral sensitivity of each channel.

fields.caption: ISO Speed Ratings
fields.description: EXIF tag 34855, 0x8827. ISO Speed and ISO Latitude of the input device as specified in ISO 12232.

fields.caption: Shutter Speed Value
fields.description: EXIF tag 37377, 0x9201. Shutter speed, unit is APEX. See Annex C of the EXIF specification.

fields.caption: Aperture Value
fields.description: EXIF tag 37378, 0x9202. Lens aperture, unit is APEX.

fields.caption: Brightness Value
fields.description: EXIT tag 37379, 0x9203. Brightness, unit is APEX.

fields.caption: Exposure Bias Value
fields.description: EXIT tag 37380, 0x9204. Exposure bias, unit is APEX.

fields.caption: Max Aperture Value
fields.description: EXIT tag 37381, 0x9205. Smallest F number of lens, in APEX.

fields.caption: Subject Distance
fields.description: EXIT tag 37382, 0x9206. Distance to subject, in meters.

fields.caption: Metering Mode
fields.description: EXIT tag 37383, 0x9207. Metering mode: 0=unknown, 1=Average, 2=CenterWeightedAverage, 3=Spot, 4=MultiSpot, 5=Pattern, 6=Partial, 255=other.

fields.caption: Light Source
fields.description: EXIT tag 37384, 0x9208. EXIF tag 0x.

fields.caption: Flash
fields.description: EXIT tag 37385, 0x9209. Strobe light (flash) source data.

fields.caption: Focal Length
fields.description: EXIT tag 37386, 0x920A. Focal length of the lens, in millimeters.

fields.caption: Subject Area
fields.description: EXIT tag 37386, 0x9214. The location and area of the main subject in the overall scene.

fields.caption: Flash Energy
fields.description: EXIT tag 41483, 0xA20B. Strobe energy during image capture.

fields.caption: Focal Plane X Resolution
fields.description: EXIT tag 41486, 0xA20E. Horizontal focal resolution, measured pixels per unit.

fields.caption: Focal Plane Y Resolution
fields.description: EXIT tag 41487, 0xA20F. Vertical focal resolution, measured in pixels per unit.

fields.caption: Focal Plane Resolution Unit
fields.description: EXIT tag 41488, 0xA210. Unit used for FocalPlaneXResolution and FocalPlaneYResolution. 2=inches 3=centimeters.

fields.caption: Subject Location
fields.description: EXIT tag 41492, 0xA214. Location of the main subject of the scene. The first value is the horizontal pixel  and the second value is the vertical pixel at which the main subject appears.

fields.caption: Exposure Index
fields.description: EXIT tag 41493, 0xA215. Exposure index of input device.

fields.caption: Sensing Method
fields.description: EXIT tag 41495, 0xA217. Image sensor type on input device: 1=NotDefined 2=One-chip color area sensor 3=Two-chip color area sensor 4=Three-chip color area sensor 5=Color sequential area sensor 7=Trilinear sensor 8=Color sequential linear sensor.

fields.caption: File Source
fields.description: EXIT tag 41728, 0xA300. Indicates image source: 3  (DSC) is the only choice.

fields.caption: Scene Type
fields.description: EXIT tag 41729, 0xA301. Indicates the type of scene: 1 (directly photographed image) is the only choice.

fields.caption: Custom Rendered
fields.description: EXIT tag 41985, 0xA401. Indicates the use of special processing on image data: 0=Normal process 1=Custom process

fields.caption: Exposure Mode
fields.description: EXIT tag 41986, 0xA402. Indicates the exposure mode set when the image was shot: 0=Auto exposure 1=Manual exposure 2=Auto bracket

fields.caption: White Balance
fields.description: EXIT tag 41987, 0xA403. Indicates the white balance mode set when the image was shot: 0=Auto white balance 1=Manual white balance

fields.caption: Digital Zoom Ratio
fields.description: EXIT tag 41988, 0xA404. Indicates the digital zoom ratio when the image was shot.

fields.caption: Focal Length In 35 mm Film
fields.description: EXIT tag 41989, 0xA405. Indicates the equivalent focal length assuming a 35mm film camera, in mm. A value of 0 means the focal length is unknown. Note that this tag differs from the FocalLength tag.

fields.caption: Scene Capture Type
fields.description: EXIT tag 41990, 0xA406. Indicates the type of scene that was shot: 0=Standard 1=Landscape 2=portrait 3=Night scene

fields.caption: Gain Control
fields.description: EXIT tag 41991, 0xA407. Indicates the degree of overall image gain adjustment: 0=None 1=Low gain up 2=High gain up 3=Low gain down 4=High gain down

fields.caption: Contrast
fields.description: EXIT tag 41992, 0xA408. Indicates the direction of contrast processing applied by the camera: 0=Normal 1=Soft 2=Hard

fields.caption: Saturation
fields.description: EXIT tag 41993, 0xA409. Indicates the direction of saturation processing applied by the camera: 0=Normal 1=Low saturation 2=High saturation

fields.caption: Sharpness
fields.description: EXIT tag 41994, 0xA40A. Indicates the direction of sharpness processing applied by the camera: 0=Normal 1=Soft 2=Hard

fields.caption: Device Setting Description
fields.description: EXIT tag 41995, 0xA40B. Indicates information on the picture-taking conditions of a particular camera model.

fields.caption: Subject Distance Range
fields.description: EXIT tag 41996, 0xA40C. Indicates the distance to the subject: 0=Unknown 1=Macro 2=Close view 3=Distant view

fields.caption: Image Unique ID
fields.description: EXIF tag 42016, 0xA420. An identifier assigned uniquely to each image. It is recorded as a 32 character ASCII string, equivalent to hexadecimal notation and 128-bit fixed length.

fields.caption: GPS Version ID
fields.description: GPS tag 0, 0x00. A decimal encoding of each of  the four EXIF bytes with period separators. The current value is "2.0.0.0".

fields.caption: GPS Latitude
fields.description: GPS tag 2, 0x02 (position) and 1, 0x01 (North/South). Indicates latitude.

fields.caption: GPS Longitude
fields.description: GPS tag 4, 0x04 (position) and 3, 0x03  (East/West). Indicates longitude.

fields.caption: GPS Altitude Ref
fields.description: GPS tag 5, 0x05. Indicates whether the altitude is above or below sea level: 0=Above sea level 1=Below sea level

fields.caption: GPS Altitude
fields.description: GPS tag 6, 0x06. Indicates altitude in meters.

fields.caption: GPS Time Stamp
fields.description: GPS tag 29 (date), 0x1D, and, and GPS tag 7 (time), 0x07. Time stamp of GPS data, in Coordinated Universal Time.

fields.caption: GPS Satellites
fields.description: GPS tag 8, 0x08. Satellite information, format is unspecified.

fields.caption: GPS Status
fields.description: GPS tag 9, 0x09. Status of GPS receiver at image creation time: A=measurement in progress V=measurement is interoperability

fields.caption: GPS Measure Mode
fields.description: GPS tag 10, 0x0A. GPS measurement mode, Text type: 2=two-dimensional measurement 3=three-dimensional measurement

fields.caption: GPS DOP
fields.description: GPS tag 11, 0x0B. Degree of precision for GPS data.

fields.caption: GPS Speed Ref
fields.description: GPS tag 12, 0x0C. Units used to speed measurement: K=kilometers per hour M=miles per hour N=Knots

fields.caption: GPS Speed
